IfThenElse
==========

This is a small ifthenelse program.
It executes one or multiple chains.

A chain is defined like this:

1 Trigger:   Wait until a certain events happens.
2 Check:     Do a check.
  TRUE:      Execute Then Action
  FALSE:     Execute Else Action.
  NO_CHANGE: Do nothing.
3. return to 1.

A chain is an action. So it is possible to nest the loops.
(beside the trigger).

An example chain (very simple):
~~~~~
<interface>
	<object class="IfThenElseChain" id="mpc_chain">
		<child type="trigger">
			<object class="IfThenElseExternalToolTrigger" id="mpc_trigger">
				<property name="cmd">mpc idle player</property>
			</object>
		</child>
		<child type="if">
			<object class="IfThenElseTrueCheck" id="mpc_check"/>
		</child>
		<child type="then">
			<object class="IfThenElseExternalToolAction" id="mpc_activate_action">
				<property name="cmd">Scripts/mpc-notify.sh</property>
			</object>
		</child>
	</object>
</interface>
~~~~~

This calls "mpc idle", if it returns. It calls Scripts/mpc-notify.sh.
